      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Tariffs are a classic tool for protecting domestic industries by raising the cost of foreign goods, which forces local companies to compete on home soil. However, this protectionism ultimately hurts consumers because they pay higher prices for everything from electronics to clothing, while the government collects the revenue as a windfall for the treasury. While some argue these measures boost manufacturing jobs, the economic reality is that they create inefficiencies and reduce overall consumer welfare in the long run.",
